Review saved. Here's a summary of the findings:

**4 BUGs, 3 QUESTIONs** found in `protocol_v2.go`:

| # | Type | Severity | Lines | Description |
|---|------|----------|-------|-------------|
| 1 | BUG | Critical | 316-321 | DeflateLevel always 0 for positive client values — missing `else` branch means client's requested level is never assigned |
| 2 | BUG | High | 483, 505, 643 | Unsafe pointer cast on message ID without length validation — out-of-bounds memory read if client sends short ID |
| 3 | BUG | Medium | 91-96 | IOLoop exits without waiting for messagePump goroutine — race condition on cleanup |
| 4 | BUG | Medium | 229-233 | Disabled OutputBufferTimeout/Heartbeat leaves stopped ticker instead of nil — violates nil-channel idiom |
| 5 | QUESTION | Low | 243 | Heartbeat.C assumed always initialized — panics if clientTimeout is 0 |
| 6 | QUESTION | Low | 428 | AddClient return value discarded |
| 7 | QUESTION | Low | 402 | SUB allowed without IDENTIFY (no StateConnected gate) |

**Assessment: FIX FIRST** — the DeflateLevel bug silently breaks compression, and the unsafe cast is a memory safety issue.
